        <div class="info-callout">
          <p><strong>NIIT thresholds are not inflation-adjusted.</strong> Unlike capital gains brackets, the Net Investment Income Tax thresholds ($200,000 single, $250,000 married jointly) are set by statute and do not change with inflation unless Congress acts. The 3.8% NIIT is expected to apply at the same income levels in 2026.</p>
